06/04/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev announced on Wednesday (5 April) that he would ask parliament this week to lift the immunity enjoyed by seven deputies who are being investigated for abuse of office, corruption and other crimes.
He named no names and denied that his move was timed to coincide with an upcoming visit by EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn.
In other news, there was a strong explosion late Wednesday evening outside prominent investigative journalist Vasil Ivanov's flat.
Neither he nor other family members were injured.
Ivanov works for Nova TV.
(Sega, Monitor - 06/04/06)
